==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Elohist
<hw>E*lo"hist</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>The writer, or one
of the writers, of the passages of the Old Testament, notably those of
the Pentateuch, which are characterized by the use of <xex>Elohim</xex>
instead of <xex>Jehovah</xex>, as the name of the Supreme Being; --
distinguished from <contr>Jehovist</contr>.</def> <rj><au>S.
Davidson.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Elohistic</ent>⟦br⟧
